getting cold, okay?

268
00:13:53,534 --> 00:13:56,576
Jo's gonna have
to get back to you.

269
00:13:56,577 --> 00:13:58,658
This is my time with you.

270
00:13:58,659 --> 00:14:00,933
I don't want to share it.

271
00:14:00,934 --> 00:14:02,120
Please?

272
00:14:09,647 --> 00:14:12,658
Uh, Alison, I'll call you
tomorrow, first thing, okay?

273
00:14:12,658 --> 00:14:15,091
And don't leave Hong Kong
until I call you back.

274
00:14:15,092 --> 00:14:16,470
Sure.

275
00:14:16,471 --> 00:14:17,783
Whenever.

276
00:14:17,783 --> 00:14:18,969
Goodbye.

277
00:14:18,970 --> 00:14:23,389
♪ ♪

278
00:14:24,414 --> 00:14:27,041
♪ ♪

279
00:14:28,802 --> 00:14:32,615
♪ ♪

280
00:14:36,716 --> 00:14:39,501
♪ ♪

281
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:42,736
It's funny how things
work out, isn't it?

282
00:14:42,738 --> 00:14:43,697
You're on that side
of the glass,

283
00:14:43,698 --> 00:14:45,235
and I'm a free man.

284
00:14:45,235 --> 00:14:46,548
How the hell did you get out?

285
00:14:46,549 --> 00:14:49,432
We'll swap prison
stories another time.

286
00:14:49,432 --> 00:14:50,937
Right now, all you need to know

287
00:14:50,937 --> 00:14:54,236
is that your bail's
been set at 200 grand.

288
00:14:54,238 --> 00:14:55,840
And I'm willing to play banker.

289
00:14:55,841 --> 00:14:59,202
♪ ♪

290
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:15,020
Shower? You're on.

291
00:15:15,022 --> 00:15:17,038
Billy, wait up.

292
00:15:17,539 --> 00:15:18,821
Hey, Jo.

293
00:15:18,822 --> 00:15:20,711
Can I talk to you privately?

294
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,279
I'll jump in the shower.

295
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:24,844
I'll be there in a minute.

296
00:15:24,844 --> 00:15:28,431
Nice to see you again, Jo.

297
00:15:28,432 --> 00:15:30,832
I take it you two
are seeing each other?

298
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:32,788
Yeah, I guess you
could say that.

299
00:15:32,788 --> 00:15:34,323
That's kind of quick, isn't it?

300
00:15:34,325 --> 00:15:37,720
I mean, Alison's only
been gone a few days.

301
00:15:37,721 --> 00:15:39,385
She still loves you, Billy.

302
00:15:39,386 --> 00:15:41,019
No, she doesn't.

303
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,302
And it doesn't matter,
'cause I don't love her,

304
00:15:42,302 --> 00:15:43,934
I love Brooke.

305
00:15:43,936 --> 00:15:45,056
We're getting married
on Saturday.

306
00:15:45,057 --> 00:15:46,048
What?

307
00:15:46,049 --> 00:15:47,138
Look, I know it's news to you,

308
00:15:47,139 --> 00:15:48,578
but what Brooke and
I have is real,

309
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:50,629
and when it's real, it
happens fast, you know?

310
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:52,648
That's a pretty convenient
rationalization.

311
00:15:52,649 --> 00:15:54,826
The wedding's at 4:00 at Brooke's
house in Pasadena, all right?

312
00:15:54,827 --> 00:15:56,812
There's an invitation
in your mailbox.

313
00:15:56,813 --> 00:15:59,471
Billy, anyone can see
you're on the rebound.

314
00:15:59,471 --> 00:16:02,578
Well, this isn't
anybody's business.

315
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:05,269
Jo, I understand
your loyalty to Alison.

316
00:16:05,269 --> 00:16:06,903
You know, you wanted things
to work out between us

317
00:16:06,903 --> 00:16:08,344
and it just didn't.

318
00:16:08,345 --> 00:16:10,072
I think you're making a mistake.

319
00:16:10,073 --> 00:16:12,125
Well, then I guess you
shouldn't be RSVP-ing.

320
00:16:18,821 --> 00:16:22,440
♪ ♪

321
00:16:25,578 --> 00:16:27,628
Well, it must
feel great to be home.

322
00:16:27,629 --> 00:16:30,831
Yeah, I just wish I didn't still
have a noose hanging around my neck.

323
00:16:30,832 --> 00:16:32,784
I hate women.

324
00:16:32,786 --> 00:16:36,086
Correction... I hate all the women
I've ever been in love with.

325
00:16:36,086 --> 00:16:37,590
So, how long were you in jail?

326
00:16:37,591 --> 00:16:39,544
In and out in three days.

327
00:16:39,546 --> 00:16:41,691
I've been following my lawyer's
advice and laying low.

328
00:16:41,692 --> 00:16:42,780
Which reminds me, I have
an appointment for you.

329
00:16:42,782 --> 00:16:44,381
He can see you at 5:00.

330
00:16:44,383 --> 00:16:46,432
Uh, thanks, but at the
moment I can't even afford

331
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:49,442
the rent on this beach house, much
less high-rent legal counsel.

332
00:16:49,443 --> 00:16:51,140
I can.

333
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:52,582
He got me out with a
slap on the wrist...

334
00:16:52,584 --> 00:16:55,529
2,000 hours of community
service in a free clinic.

335
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:56,875
And you were guilty.

336
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:58,317
Imagine what he could do for me.

337
00:16:58,317 --> 00:17:00,847
Consider it a package
deal, Mancini.

338
00:17:00,849 --> 00:17:02,897
Legal fees and bail.

339
00:17:02,898 --> 00:17:04,179
That's very generous.

340
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,811
But what's in it for you?

341
00:17:05,813 --> 00:17:08,343
I've got a medical board hearing
at the end of the week.

342
00:17:08,344 --> 00:17:10,393
They want to yank my license.
You're kidding.

343
00:17:10,394 --> 00:17:12,474
Just because you tried to
kill one of your patients?

344
00:17:12,476 --> 00:17:15,038
I've done a lot of things in
my past that I'm not proud of.

345
00:17:15,038 --> 00:17:16,383
And I'm paying for them now.

346
00:17:16,384 --> 00:17:18,498
But I'm a changed man
and I'm a good doctor.

347
00:17:18,499 --> 00:17:20,259
Now, tell me you can't
relate to that.

348
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:21,765
I want you to go
before the board,

349
00:17:21,766 --> 00:17:23,077
recant your prior testimony

350
00:17:23,078 --> 00:17:26,473
regarding Amanda's
emergency appendectomy.

351
00:17:26,474 --> 00:17:28,717
Now, you wipe my slate
clean, I wipe yours,

352
00:17:28,718 --> 00:17:31,278
and we both start out fresh,

353
00:17:31,279 --> 00:17:34,193
maybe even as partners
in our own practice,

354
00:17:34,194 --> 00:17:36,757
like we always talked about.

355
00:17:36,758 --> 00:17:39,030
So all I have to do
is backpedal a little,

356
00:17:39,031 --> 00:17:40,311
and I get my name cleared

357
00:17:40,313 --> 00:17:44,028
and a chance to hang
a shingle in Beverly Hills.

358
00:17:44,029 --> 00:17:45,405
I hate to admit it,

359
00:17:45,406 --> 00:17:47,681
but this is starting
to sound very interesting.

360
00:17:47,682 --> 00:17:49,089
What can I say?

361
00:17:49,090 --> 00:17:52,580
I got a soft spot
for you, Mancini.

362
00:17:52,582 --> 00:17:53,830
We're two of a kind.

363
00:17:58,701 --> 00:18:00,718
God grant me the serenity

364
00:18:00,719 --> 00:18:04,497
to accept the things
I cannot change,

365
00:18:04,498 --> 00:18:08,054
courage to change
the things I can,

366
00:18:08,055 --> 00:18:10,712
and the wisdom to
know the difference.

367
00:18:16,542 --> 00:18:18,528
Excuse me.

368
00:18:18,528 --> 00:18:20,321
I related to everything
you shared.

369
00:18:20,323 --> 00:18:21,796
It took me two years
to get used to living

370
00:18:21,797 --> 00:18:23,781
this far away from home.

371
00:18:23,782 --> 00:18:25,352
Ian Sinclair.

372
00:18:25,353 --> 00:18:26,984
We met at the luncheon
the other day?

373
00:18:26,986 --> 00:18:28,426
Oh, right.

374
00:18:28,426 --> 00:18:30,797
You're in Armstrong's
sales division.

375
00:18:30,798 --> 00:18:33,262
Don't tell anyone in the
company I'm this homesick.

376
00:18:33,263 --> 00:18:34,833
My lips are sealed.

377
00:18:34,834 --> 00:18:35,953
Making friends helps.

378
00:18:35,954 --> 00:18:37,042
And having a sponsor.

379
00:18:37,044 --> 00:18:38,548
Do you have one?

380
00:18:38,549 --> 00:18:39,862
Not in Hong Kong.

381
00:18:39,863 --> 00:18:42,328
Well, you do now,
if you want one.

382
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:45,532
I'm five years sober and I
speak pretty good English.

383
00:18:45,534 --> 00:18:47,519
Sure, that'd be terrific.

384
00:18:47,519 --> 00:18:49,088
I know how rough it can be.

385
00:18:49,089 --> 00:18:50,657
So I'll be checking on you.

386
00:18:50,659 --> 00:18:54,855
And feel free to call,
anytime, day or night.

387
00:18:54,855 --> 00:18:56,038
I doubt I'll be doing that,

388
00:18:56,039 --> 00:18:57,739
but thanks anyway.

389
00:19:05,618 --> 00:19:07,667
How could they foreclose on you?

390
00:19:07,669 --> 00:19:10,711
Sydney invested
$100,000 of my money

391
00:19:10,711 --> 00:19:12,663
in Mancini Designs
just last month!

392
00:19:12,664 --> 00:19:14,650
I used the money to
pay off our creditors,

393
00:19:14,651 --> 00:19:16,348
but it still wasn't enough!

394
00:19:16,349 --> 00:19:18,046
Maybe if you hadn't been so busy

395
00:19:18,047 --> 00:19:19,423
every time I tried to tell you
the business was in trouble,

396
00:19:19,424 --> 00:19:21,217
Michael, it wouldn't
come as such a shock.

397
00:19:21,218 --> 00:19:23,364
Oh, don't make me the whipping
boy for your failure.

398
00:19:23,365 --> 00:19:25,222
This is on your head, Jane!

399
00:19:30,827 --> 00:19:32,588
Half of LA is
already hard at work,

400
00:19:32,589 --> 00:19:34,256
and you're still in
your bathrobe?

401
00:19:34,257 --> 00:19:35,856
You know, Jane, if you
worked a little harder,

402
00:19:35,857 --> 00:19:38,676
you'd be able to pay DD the fees
you owe from your last campaign.

403
00:19:40,118 --> 00:19:41,527
What's he doing out of jail?

404
00:19:41,528 --> 00:19:43,096
Oh, he is out on bail,

405
00:19:43,096 --> 00:19:45,211
courtesy of your
ex-boyfriend, Peter Burns.

406
00:19:45,211 --> 00:19:46,779
That's impossible.

407
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:49,534
Peter should be even farther
down the river than you.

408
00:19:49,535 --> 00:19:50,881
He has a great lawyer.

409
00:19:50,882 --> 00:19:52,898
Check that: We have
a great lawyer.

410
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,084
I don't believe this.

411
00:19:54,085 --> 00:19:55,621
What kind of country
is this that they let

412
00:19:55,622 --> 00:19:58,280
two vile criminals like
you out of jail?

413
00:19:58,281 --> 00:19:59,752
No, don't tell me,
'cause I don't want to know.

414
00:19:59,753 --> 00:20:01,547
Stay the hell away
from me, Michael.

415
00:20:01,548 --> 00:20:03,502
Oh, ask me to do something hard.

416
00:20:05,393 --> 00:20:06,577
You're flattering yourself

417
00:20:06,577 --> 00:20:08,755
if you think I'd risk
a jail term for you.

418
00:20:08,756 --> 00:20:10,421
I'm an innocent man,

419
00:20:10,422 --> 00:20:12,086
and once I prove it,

420
00:20:12,087 --> 00:20:14,905
I'm gonna slap you with a
defamation of character suit

421
00:20:14,906 --> 00:20:16,699
that'll drain your
bank account so fast

422
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:18,461
that you'll be in chapter 11,

423
00:20:18,462 --> 00:20:19,807
just like Janie here.

424
00:20:23,426 --> 00:20:25,285
What's this about chapter 11?

425
00:20:25,286 --> 00:20:26,950
The bank seized all my assets.

426
00:20:26,951 --> 00:20:28,455
I'm in foreclosure.

427
00:20:28,457 --> 00:20:31,019
And, unfortunately, DD is
gonna have to get in line

428
00:20:31,019 --> 00:20:32,778
with all the other
bill collectors.

429
00:20:32,779 --> 00:20:34,286
How devastating for you, Jane.

430
00:20:34,287 --> 00:20:36,593
But don't worry about
its impact on DD,

431
00:20:36,594 --> 00:20:38,578
because as of
2:00 this afternoon,

432
00:20:38,579 --> 00:20:40,019
the president of
Mackenzie Hart Designs

433
00:20:40,019 --> 00:20:43,830
will be in my office signing
his exclusive contract.

434
00:20:43,832 --> 00:20:45,753
Mackenzie Hart?

435
00:20:45,755 --> 00:20:47,323
She was my inspiration.

436
00:20:47,324 --> 00:20:49,213
I mean, she was the reason
I became a designer.

437
00:20:49,214 --> 00:20:51,070
I can see how she would
be, considering her skill

438
00:20:51,072 --> 00:20:52,961
in choosing savvy
business partners.

439
00:20:52,961 --> 00:20:55,044
Too bad you didn't have someone
like Richard Hart behind you.

440
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:56,195
Introduce me.

441
00:20:56,197 --> 00:20:58,278
Sorry, no can do.

442
00:20:58,278 --> 00:21:00,039
Then at least show him
my designs.

443
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:02,058
Trust me, I don't think Richard
Hart would be interested

444
00:21:02,059 --> 00:21:04,781
in the pencil scrawls
of a bankrupt wannabe.

445
00:21:04,782 --> 00:21:06,096
So the ink's not even dry yet,

446
00:21:06,096 --> 00:21:07,826
and you're already
his spokesperson?

447
00:21:07,826 --> 00:21:09,682
In this case, yes.

448
00:21:09,683 --> 00:21:11,669
Well, unlike you, I have
a job to get to.

449
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:14,103
Bye.

450
00:21:14,104 --> 00:21:17,468
♪ ♪

451
00:21:21,086 --> 00:21:22,336
I'll have the sketches
for you next week

452
00:21:22,336 --> 00:21:23,873
and we can get
together for lunch.

453
00:21:23,874 --> 00:21:25,089
Fine. Just call my office. Okay.

454
00:21:25,090 --> 00:21:26,243
Mr. Hart.

455
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:28,807
Hi, uh, my name is Jane Mancini.

456
00:21:28,807 --> 00:21:30,792
What are you doing here? If I could
have just a minute of your time.

457
00:21:30,794 --> 00:21:31,786
How dare you.

458
00:21:31,787 --> 00:21:33,323
Amanda, what's this all about?

459
00:21:33,324 --> 00:21:34,669
It's about what I can
do for you, Mr. Hart...

460
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:35,630
See, I'm a designer.

461
00:21:35,631 --> 00:21:37,070
A desperate, out-of-work one.

462
00:21:37,072 --> 00:21:38,736
I apologize for this
woman's behavior.

463
00:21:38,737 --> 00:21:40,049
No problem.

464
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:41,107
I'll see you next week.

465
00:21:41,108 --> 00:21:42,388
Okay. Mr. Hart, please, just...

466
00:21:42,388 --> 00:21:43,798
You are not going anywhere.

467
00:21:43,798 --> 00:21:44,824
Careful!

468
00:21:44,824 --> 00:21:47,000
Wait! Ah!

469
00:21:47,001 --> 00:21:48,731
Amanda, are you all right?

470
00:21:48,732 --> 00:21:50,942
Look, um, I've never done
anything like this before,

471
00:21:50,942 --> 00:21:51,903
but Mr. Hart...
You know, I'm sure

472
00:21:51,903 --> 00:21:53,407
that you're a good designer,

473
00:21:53,409 --> 00:21:55,523
but I leave all the hiring
to our personnel office.

474
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:57,220
I had my own company
until yesterday.

475
00:21:57,221 --> 00:21:59,366
And I think if you just
took a look at my designs,

476
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:01,416
you might see that...

477
00:22:01,417 --> 00:22:04,652
Forget it. Sorry to
have bothered you.

478
00:22:04,653 --> 00:22:06,990
Don't be.

479
00:22:06,991 --> 00:22:10,130
If my looking at your designs
was important enough to, uh,

480
00:22:10,131 --> 00:22:12,627
knock the president
of DD on her ass,

481
00:22:12,628 --> 00:22:14,134
how can I say no?

482
00:22:14,135 --> 00:22:15,960
Drop by the office tomorrow.

483
00:22:15,961 --> 00:22:17,082
Thank you.

484
00:22:18,971 --> 00:22:20,445
Thank you so much.

485
00:22:24,738 --> 00:22:28,549
♪ ♪

486
00:22:32,394 --> 00:22:33,738
Hey, Syd.

487
00:22:33,739 --> 00:22:35,243
Michael, you're not
on the lam, are you?

488
00:22:35,244 --> 00:22:36,589
Relax, I'm out on bail.

489
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:38,606
So, what did you
find out about Kimberly?

490
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:41,810
Uh, well, I called around all
the motels around the hospital

491
00:22:41,811 --> 00:22:44,342
and found out she's
at the Casa Malibu Motel.

492
00:22:44,342 --> 00:22:45,815
Yes, and?

493
00:22:45,816 --> 00:22:48,122
And, I think you're wrong
about her this time, Michael.

494
00:22:48,123 --> 00:22:50,106
She was very sweet to me
when I interrogated her.

495
00:22:50,107 --> 00:22:51,580
Trust me, it was an act.

496
00:22:51,582 --> 00:22:55,424
She hates your guts almost
as much as she hates mine.

497
00:22:55,425 --> 00:22:56,385
So did you check out the room?

498
00:22:56,386 --> 00:22:57,955
No, I didn't have time.

499
00:22:57,957 --> 00:22:59,621
Maybe now that you're out
of jail, you could do it.

500
00:22:59,622 --> 00:23:01,287
Oh, right... somebody sees
me there, I'm dog meat.

501
00:23:01,288 --> 00:23:04,459
Back behind
bars in a nanosecond.

502
00:23:04,460 --> 00:23:06,636
Come on, Syd, don't
make me beg, okay?

503
00:23:06,637 --> 00:23:07,821
What if I get caught?

504
00:23:07,823 --> 00:23:08,782
You won't.

505
00:23:08,784 --> 00:23:10,384
And bring a camera.

506
00:23:10,384 --> 00:23:13,107
I think there may be dead
bodies in her bathtub.

507
00:23:13,108 --> 00:23:14,965
That's it, no, "Thanks, Syd"?

508
00:23:14,967 --> 00:23:17,336
No, "You're a real pal, Syd"?

509
00:23:17,336 --> 00:23:20,092
Sure, yeah. All of the above.

510
00:23:20,093 --> 00:23:22,108
Call me as soon as you have
something to report, okay?

511
00:23:22,109 --> 00:23:24,673
♪ ♪

512
00:23:26,082 --> 00:23:28,994
Yeah, I want a dozen
white roses.

513
00:23:28,996 --> 00:23:30,854
No, make it two.

514
00:23:30,855 --> 00:23:33,448
And I want to include
a gift card with that.

515
00:23:33,449 --> 00:23:37,422
"To Carol, just thinking of you."

516
00:23:37,422 --> 00:23:38,990
"Love..."

517
00:23:38,990 --> 00:23:42,290
No, no, write,
write, "Forever, Paul."

518
00:23:42,291 --> 00:23:44,853
And add it to my account, okay?

519
00:23:44,854 --> 00:23:46,134
Thank you.

520
00:23:47,865 --> 00:23:49,209
Are you ready?

521
00:23:49,210 --> 00:23:50,714
Are you kidding?

522
00:23:50,715 --> 00:23:52,701
Been looking forward
to seeing you all day.

523
00:23:52,701 --> 00:23:53,919
Yeah? Me, too.

524
00:24:06,796 --> 00:24:08,173
Call for you on line one.

